      "options": {
        "code": {"language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false},
        "content": "## Reading this dashboard\n\n**1. Is there an OOM kill?**\n- Top-left stat panel `OOM Kills (24h)` should be 0.\n- Loki annotation `OOM Kills (kernel-capture)` overlays the timeseries with red lines from `/var/log/kernel-capture/<node>.log`. Each line is a `Killed process N (cilium-agent)` (or whatever cgroup hit the limit).\n- If kill events line up in time with a meltdown, the suspect is **confirmed**.\n\n**2. Is Go GC thrashing near GOMEMLIMIT?**\n- The Cilium Helm chart sets `GOMEMLIMIT` env var from `resources.limits.memory`. With the recent 1Gi -> 2Gi bump the soft ceiling is 2 GiB.\n- Look at `Go GC pause (p99) per cilium-agent`. Healthy = low single-digit ms. Thrashing = repeated jumps to 50-500 ms aligned with the working-set graph nearing 1.8-1.95 GiB.\n- Mitigation: set `GOMEMLIMIT` env var explicitly to e.g. `1700MiB` so Go starts GC pacing *before* the cgroup limit; OR raise `limits.memory` further; OR shed load from talos00.\n\n**3. Is talos00 the host getting evicted?**\n- `Nodes in MemoryPressure` stat panel should be 0.\n- `Host memory % per node` — if talos00 sustains >85%, the kubelet's eviction manager will flip MemoryPressure=true and start killing low-priority pods. Cilium-agent is `system-node-critical` so it won't be evicted first, but the cluster will still wobble.\n\n**4. Where is the RAM going?**\n- `talos00 — top 10 pods by working_set_bytes` is the eviction shortlist. Anything that is not control-plane / cilium / kubelet / etcd is a candidate for `nodeSelector`-ing off talos00.\n\n## If suspect is confirmed\n\n1. **Short term**: drop GOMEMLIMIT below the cgroup limit\n   ```yaml\n   # infrastructure/base/cilium/values.yaml\n   extraEnv:\n     - name: GOMEMLIMIT\n       value: \"1700MiB\"\n   ```\n2. **Medium term**: stop scheduling apps on the CP\n   ```yaml\n   # talos machine config (controlplane.yaml)\n   cluster:\n     allowSchedulingOnControlPlanes: false\n   ```\n3. **Long term**: HA control plane (3 CP nodes) — see `docs/05-runbooks/ha-control-plane-migration.md`.\n\n## If suspect is rejected\n\n- All cilium-agents < 70% limit, no OOM kills, no MemoryPressure → memory is not the bottleneck. Move on to the other suspects (BPF map overflow, conntrack, etcd snapshot timing, etc.).",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Runbook",
      "type": "text"
    }
